latestIgtvVideos.title: You are your own standard of beauty!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
You don't need to change yourself to fit in. There are no beauty standards. There is no society to tell you how you should look, we create the society so don't let society create you.

You were not born to hate the
body that you live in, but it is not your fault for wishing you look differently than you do.

The judgments that people have cast on you for looking a certain way is nothing more than just a projection of their own wounds-wounds that were sown generations ago, wounds that are not healed.

When you fully accept the cellulite on your thighs and the stretch marks on your bum, it becomes an empowering experience - not just for you but for all humans that were once told that they were anything but perfect.
The colour of your skin, the extra hair on the side of your chin, dark circles on your face, pimple on your skin, the cellulite that rests so gracefully on the back of your legs makes you, YOU.

So you don't have to try so hard to fit in.

START LOVING YOUR FLAWS BECAUSE THEY MAKE YOU, YOU!
Why fit in? When you can be you. 
.
.
Music - TRY @colbiecaillat 
Produced, directed, filmed and edited by me. 
.
.
.
.
.

.

latestPosts.caption:
I still can’t believe the day has come where I finally get to write this. It’s going to be a long one because it has earned it. I’m already so emotional, but here we go.

Nine years ago, we were just two kids, figuring out life and love together. It feels like just yesterday that we met in college, unsure of where life would take us, but knowing deep down that this connection was special. We were young, full of dreams, and maybe a little naïve about love—but we learned, we grew, and we built something truly beautiful. And here we are—nine years later, standing at the beginning of forever.

These years have seen us through highs, lows, and everything in between. There were days when the distance felt impossible, when the waiting seemed endless, but in every challenge, I found more reasons to love you. There were moments when I doubted this day would come, when the distance felt too overwhelming. But here we are, stronger than ever, with a love that’s more real and profound than I can put into words.

Being apart for so long wasn’t easy, but it taught us what true love and patience really mean. Even with miles between us, we kept growing together, kept our connection strong. Now, standing together, I can say every second apart was worth it. We didn’t just survive the distance; we thrived because of it.

When Rohan asked, ‘Will you marry me?’, I wasn’t just emotional—I was overwhelmed. It wasn’t just a question about spending our lives together; it was a promise to continue sharing our dreams, our vulnerabilities, and the unbreakable bond we’ve built. It was about holding on to the love that brought us here and embracing all the moments that lie ahead. I was shivering, my heart racing, and I couldn’t even say ‘yes’ properly because I was so overwhelmed. Tears fell before I could speak, my makeup was a mess, but none of it mattered. In that moment, everything I had ever dreamed of, everything we had worked for, was right there. It was the culmination of years of love, patience, and growth, coming together in the most perfect way. And as I looked at him, there was no doubt in my mind—this is exactly where I’m meant to be. Forever ✨

29/08/2024 - forever etched 💍❤️

Nine years ago, on this very day, I posted my first ever Instagram post as a creator. Little did I know that one small step would completely change my life. This journey has been the most special part of my life, and it will always hold a very, very close place in my heart.

I’ve grown so much as a person during these years. I’ve built a life that little Dewanshi could never even imagine. I still pinch myself sometimes when I think about working with my dream brands, being honored by so many colleges, events, and people, getting featured in the media, on billboards, being interviewed on FM radio, and even collaborating with celebrities. It’s crazy how life can surprise you when you follow your passion.

When I started, I didn’t know anything about fashion or makeup. I just knew one thing—I wanted to be a fashion blogger. So, I learned everything from scratch. I taught myself makeup, I figured out fashion trends—all through the internet. I didn’t have all the answers, but I had a dream, and that was enough.

If there’s one thing I’ve learned, it’s this: you don’t need to have it all figured out to start. If you have a dream, take that first step. It’s hard, yes, but it’s so, so worth it. The universe has a funny way of aligning things when you truly go after what you want.

Today, I just feel incredibly grateful—to this platform, to all of you who have supported me, and to life for letting me live this dream every single day. It’s wild to think that I get to click pictures and call it my job. Isn’t that insane? I love this life, and I hope each one of you finds something that makes you feel the same.

Here’s to nine years of growing, learning, and living a dream I didn’t even know was possible. ❤️ Thank you for being a part of it.
